{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Generate Test Coverage Report",
  "description": "Manually triggered hook that runs the full test suite with coverage, generates a timestamped coverage report and gap analysis, and saves them to docs/test-reports/. Also updates the audit log.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Generate a comprehensive test coverage report for this project. Steps: 1) Detect the project's test framework and coverage tool from config files. 2) Run the full test suite with coverage enabled. 3) Parse the coverage output. 4) Create a timestamped coverage report at docs/test-reports/coverage/[ISO-8601-timestamp].md following the format in the test evidence policy (include summary table, files below threshold, critical path coverage, uncovered lines). 5) Copy the report to docs/test-reports/coverage/latest.md. 6) Scan the codebase for untested modules and exports, then create a gap analysis report at docs/test-reports/gap-analysis/[ISO-8601-timestamp].md. 7) Append entries to docs/test-reports/audit-log.md for both the coverage report and gap analysis. Create the docs/test-reports directory structure if it doesn't exist."
  }
}